replyContent: CRACKSHOT supports lasers with up to 50ms in pulse duration (which is visible by both 30 and 60 fps). Our app supports at least a 16.6ms on most devices. Most lasers including CRACKSHOT are at least 50ms, with the exception of LaserHIT brand which has a 1ms pulse duration. Our list of supported lasers is available on our app store page.

content: Our department found this app to be the best - easy to use and comprehensive.
Several uncounted shots even after adjusting the light
replyContent: Hi moto, please try increasing sensitivity from the settings menu. Adjusting the light can help because in bright areas, the phone can go into a bright light mode which causes the laser to look "white" instead of red. We do handle this in app, but results vary by phone phone. For this reason, detection works when targets are out of direct sunlight.

content: Great looking app but it malfunctions alot. It marked hits nowhere close to where they showed up on paper. If there is any shadows or movements it records hit. Hopefully with some development it will be better
replyContent: Hi James, Thank you for trying out our app. CRACKSHOT is uses changes in lighting to determine where hits are generated. As such, it works best with interior rooms, as external lighting (say from a window with shadows outside) will cause false positives. Try moving your targets to an interior wall and close your window blinds. Thanks!
